Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, that is the shot of the IPL so far to me! Short outside off, Suryakumar Yadav is hopping when he makes contact - his legs are in the air - and he upper-cuts with a flourish, hits it on top of the bounce and uses Umesh Yadav's extra pace to send it into the crowd at third man. Stunning shot. The last two balls ruins Umesh Yadav's fine day with the ball

Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Tilak Varma, no run, comedy of errors and the catch goes down. Total miscommunication between Billings and Rahane running in from backward point. Short and pacey, another top-edge on the pull, Billings runs in and it's his catch, but there's no calling, Rahane comes for it and then at the last moment is not sure - or was he put-off by Billings? - hesitates and Billings has not gone for it now, Rahane dives forward in a desperate attempt to catch but does not even get his fingertips to it. Umesh Yadav is understandably unhappy

Commentary Text: Chakaravarthy to Brevis, out Stumped!! Sharp work from Billings and Brevis has to go. Slower and the seam rolls all over the place as it comes out of Chakaravarthy's hand, Brevis slogsweeps and misses it from outside off, he stretched forward to play the shot and the back foot was outside the crease, doesn't get it back but Billings had the bails off in a flash with minimal followthrough. Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Rohit, out Caught by Billings!! What a fine catch that is. Varun at short fine backpedalling made it as tough as possible for Billings, but the Englishman keeps his eyes on it and takes the skier. Reward for Umesh Yadav's consistency. Short and pacey outside off, Rohit takes it on, but is rushed and the top-edge seems to be landing in front of Varun who was gingerly looking to catch. But Billings ran back and took it.
